    "actor_description": "Something about it lands gentle. My attention stops scrambling and just rests-on shape, texture, the quiet rightness of how parts fit together. I feel my shoulders drop as if I'd been bracing without noticing; a slow exhale slides out of me like permission. I don't want to solve it or use it-I just want to stay with it for a moment and let the inside of my chest unclench.",
    "description_text": "{actor} slows down as they take it in. Their face softens; their gaze lingers instead of darting, and their posture eases-shoulders lowering, hands loosening, movements turning unhurried and careful. They pause in a way that reads like savoring: not frozen, not distracted-simply letting the moment settle into them.",
